## EDA Workflow

This project uses the @ai-eda toolkit with Claude Code. Use these slash commands:

### 1. Specification Phase
- `/eda-spec` - Define project requirements and constraints

### 2. Component Sourcing
- `/eda-source [role]` - Research and select components (e.g., `/eda-source main-mcu`)
- `/eda-library [part]` - Fetch KiCad libraries from EasyEDA/LCSC

### 3. Schematic Design
- `/eda-schematic` - Create and populate schematic
- `/eda-wiring` - Wire connections between components

### 4. PCB Layout
- `/eda-pcb-place` - Place components on the PCB
- `/eda-pcb-route` - Route traces

### 5. Validation & Manufacturing
- `/eda-validate` - Run DRC and verify design
- `/eda-export [format]` - Generate manufacturing files (jlcpcb, pcbway, oshpark)

## MCP Tools

This project has access to:
- **jlc**: Component search, datasheet retrieval, library conversion
- **kicad-pcb**: PCB operations (placement, routing, DRC, export)
- **kicad-sch**: Schematic operations (component placement, wiring)

### Tool Naming Convention
- PCB tools: `mcp__kicad-pcb__*` (e.g., `mcp__kicad-pcb__place_component`)
- Schematic tools: `mcp__kicad-sch__*` (e.g., `mcp__kicad-sch__add_component`)
- Component tools: `mcp__jlc__*` (e.g., `mcp__jlc__search_components`)

## Important Notes

- Always run `/eda-validate` before `/eda-export`
- Check component stock levels before finalizing selections
- Commit changes after each major milestone
- Keep datasheets for all selected components
